==English==
===Etymology===
[[Blend]] of '''[[chill out|chill (out)]]''' and '''[[relax]]''' (''see [http://www.elmwoodstrip.com/elmwood/blogDisplay/index.php?u=hodown&id=46 here] for the purported coiner'')
[[Category:Portmanteaus]]

===Pronunciation===
*chĭlăksʹ /ʧɪˈlæks/<!-- (/ʧɨˈlæksɨz/, /ʧɨˈlæksɪŋ/, /ʧɨˈlækst/)-->, /<tt>tSI"l{ks</tt>/

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-sibilant|chilla|x|}}
#{{slang}} To [[relax]]; to be [[laid back]]
#:''Let's watch a movie with Maria and '''chillax''' tonight.''
#{{slang}} To [[calm down]]
#:'''''Chillax''' dude, or they are going to know you are [[trip]]ping.''
#{{slang}} To [[behave]]; "Don't throw that ball at me."
#:''Oi, '''chillax''' sunshine, or there's gonna be trouble!''

====Synonyms====
*(''relax''): [[chill out]], [[relax]], [[unwind]]
*(''calm down''): [[calm down]], [[chill]], [[cool it]]
*(''behave''): be [[good]], [[behave]] (oneself)

====Antonyms====
*(''relax''): get [[worked up]], [[stress]] oneself (out)
*(''calm down''): 
*(''behave''): behave [[badly]], [[misbehave]]

